obbit\"),\n                                         tuple(\"Legolas\", 1000, null));\n\nI extract and modify the official code to demonstrate the issue.\n\nImagine that Legolas doesn't belong to any race, so we set Legolas's race to null. And then I try to assert that Legolas's race name is null. But I got the exception below,\n\njava.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException: Index: 2, Size: 2\n    at java.util.ArrayList.rangeCheck(ArrayList.java:638)\n    at java.util.ArrayList.get(ArrayList.java:414)\n    at java.util.Collections$UnmodifiableList.get(Collections.java:1369)\n    at org.assertj.core.groups.FieldsOrPropertiesExtractor.extract(FieldsOrPropertiesExtractor.java:108)\n    at org.assertj.core.groups.FieldsOrPropertiesExtractor.extract(FieldsOrPropertiesExtractor.java:60)\n    at org.assertj.core.api.AbstractObjectArrayAssert.extracting(AbstractObjectArrayAssert.java:422)\n\nIn fact, extracting deep attributes works well alone even with null, but it has a problem with tuple. Thanks in advance.\n","closed_by":{"login":"joel-costigliola","id":382613,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM4MjYxMw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/382613?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola","html_url":"https://github.com/joel-costigliola","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/received_events","type":"Us